set default deny

interface mgmt = "ens3"
interface lan = "lan0"
interface wan = "wan0"
interface backup = "backup0"

table <branch_lan> { 10.70.0.0/24 }
table <voice_hosts> { 10.70.0.20, 10.70.0.21 }
table <blocked> { 10.70.0.66, 10.70.0.67 }
table <dns_resolvers> { 1.1.1.1, 9.9.9.9 }

queue bulk on wan bandwidth 100mbit
queue voice on wan bandwidth 10mbit parent bulk
queue backup_bulk on backup bandwidth 25mbit

pass in on mgmt proto tcp from any to any port 22 keep state
pass out on mgmt from any to any keep state

nat on wan from <branch_lan> to any -> wan
nat on backup from <branch_lan> to any -> backup

block in log (all) on lan from <blocked> to any
pass in on lan proto udp from <voice_hosts> to any port 5060 queue voice keep state
pass in on lan proto udp from <voice_hosts> to any port 10000 queue voice keep state
pass in on lan proto tcp from <branch_lan> to any port 80 queue bulk route-to 198.51.100.1 (wan) keep state
pass in on lan proto tcp from <branch_lan> to any port 443 queue bulk route-to 198.51.100.1 (wan) keep state
pass in on lan proto tcp from <branch_lan> to any port 22 queue backup_bulk route-to 203.0.113.1 (backup) keep state
pass in on lan proto udp from <branch_lan> to <dns_resolvers> port 53 queue bulk keep state

block in log (all) on wan from any to any
block in log (all) on backup from any to any
block out log (user) on wan from any to any
block out log (user) on backup from any to any
